---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Paragraph from "../components/elements/Paragraph.astro";
import Main from "../components/elements/Main.astro";
import Section from "../components/elements/Section.astro";
import Subtitle from "../components/elements/Subtitle.astro";
import TopBar from "../components/TopBar.astro";
import BottomBar from "../components/BottomBar.astro";
import ToolCard from "../components/ToolCard.astro";

import ProjectCard from "../components/ProjectCard.astro";
import { type Project } from "../types/index";
import projects from "../data/projects.json";
---

<Layout title="Somtochukwu">
  <Main>
    <TopBar />
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-6 my-6 lg:my-8 xl:grid-cols-4 xl:my-12">
      <img
        src="/profile.png"
        width="200"
        height="200"
        class="object-fit rounded-md"
      />
      {/* Top Section */}
      <Section class="col-span-3 self-center">
        <Paragraph class="my-0 mb-2">
        Welcome! I'm <b>Somto :)</b>, a passionate software developer who thrives on connecting with creative minds and tackling new challenges. I'm a fast learner who adapts quickly to new environments, I value continuous learning and keep an open mind in all endeavors. Whether it's coding for fun, playing chess, or exploring videography.
            </Paragraph>
      </Section>
    </div>

    <Section class="my-2">
      <Subtitle>About Me</Subtitle>
        <Paragraph class="my-0 mb-2">
My journey in software development began during my time at Aptech Computer Education, where I led numerous projects and was honored as the best graduating student upon graduation. Though my mom once envisioned a career in neurosurgery for me, I found my true passion in programming, and I haven't looked back since.
</Paragraph>

        <Paragraph>
        I believe in giving your best and doing what you love, and this website is my way of sharing my journey, learning experiences, and fun projects with a broader audience—not just tech enthusiasts but anyone interested in creativity and innovation. What sets me apart is my curiosity and adaptability, as I continuously explore new technologies and ideas, with a particular excitement for the potential of AI. My long-term goal is to develop a SaaS product or business that solves real-world problems for the masses. In my downtime, you'll find me reading, enjoying a good nap, or creating videos that I may or may not share online. I hope this space leaves you feeling impressed and perhaps even thinking, "I have to hire this guy!"!.
        </Paragraph>
    </Section>

    {/* Tools Section */}
    <Section>
      <Subtitle>Work</Subtitle>
      <Paragraph>
        Currently, I am training over a dozen students in web design, database
        management, and other technologies at <a class="text-green-500"
          >Prime Innovation Institute Of Technology</a
        >. I also build web applications at <a
          href="https://codecamp.ng/"
          class="text-green-500">Codecamp Nigeria</a
        >. On the side, I craft websites to help small-scale businesses connect
        with their customers.
      </Paragraph>
    </Section>

    {/* Tools Section */}
    <Section>
      <Subtitle>Tools</Subtitle>
      <Paragraph>
        My primary technologies are Typescript & Python. Below are some
        languages/tools which I utilize for an efficient workflow, school
        projects or to upgrade my arsenal of tools for the right job.
      </Paragraph>
      <div
        class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-x-6 gap-y-5"
      >
        <ToolCard name="React" />
        <ToolCard name="TailwindCSS" />
        <ToolCard name="Typescript" />
        <ToolCard name="Python" />
        <ToolCard
          name="Java"
          url="https://logos-world.net/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Java-Symbol.png"
        />
        <ToolCard name="MySQL" />
        <ToolCard name="MongoDB" />
        <ToolCard name="SQLite" />
        <ToolCard name="Git" />
        <ToolCard name="Flask" />
        <ToolCard name="Linux" />
        <ToolCard name="Neovim" />
      </div>
      <div class="border-[1px] border-green-500 rounded-xl p-4 mt-5">
        <Paragraph class="prose-sm">
          Here are other tools I'm currently diving deeper into, with the intent
          to build something or to make my workflow much more efficient.
        </Paragraph>
        <div
          class={`${true ? "grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4" : ""} mt-5 gap-x-6 gap-y-5`}
        >
          <ToolCard name="FastAPI" />
          <ToolCard name="Docker" />
          <ToolCard name="PostgreSQL" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </Section>

    {/* Projects Section */}
    <Section>
      <Subtitle>Projects</Subtitle>
      <Paragraph>
        In my free time, I try to build things I could use to solve personal
        problems and sometimes just for fun. Here are some projects which aren't
        private that I have worked on for problems I face personally or for the
        sole aim to know how something works.
      </Paragraph>
      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-x-6 gap-y-8 lg:gap-8 mt-5"
      >
        {
          (projects as Project[]).map((project) => {
            return <ProjectCard project={project} />;
          })
        }
      </div>
    </Section>

    <BottomBar />
  </Main>
</Layout>
